Some authorities say that the poet‘s father was a potter‚ others, that he was a brickmaker, while others again assert that he was the servant of a travelling merchant, Magius, whose daughter, Magia Polla, he afterwards married. The childhood of ⁵ Vergil was passed amid the hills and woods that fringed the verdant banks of the Mincius, and the early association of the poet with the lovely scenery of the neighbourhood of his native town may account for the exquisite touches of pas· toral life which appear in the Eelogues and the Georgics.
